    • Field Detail

      • selector

        private Expression selector
        object describing criteria used to select documents.

      • limit

        private Integer limit
        Maximum number of results returned. Default is 25. Optional

      • skip

        private Integer skip
        Skip the first ‘n’ results, where ‘n’ is the value specified. Optional

      • sort

        private List<Sort> sort
        contains a list of field name and direction pairs

      • fields

        private List<String> fields
        specifying which fields of each object should be returned. If it is omitted, the entire object is returned.

      • useIndex

        private String useIndex
        Instruct a query to use a specific index.

      • readQuorum

        private Integer readQuorum
        Read quorum needed for the result. This defaults to 1, in which case the document found in the index is returned. If set to a higher value, each document is read from at least that many replicas before it is returned in the results. This is likely to take more time than using only the document stored locally with the index.

      • bookmark

        private String bookmark
        A string that enables you to specify which page of results you require. Used for paging through result sets. Every query returns an opaque string under the bookmark key that can then be passed back in a query to get the next page of results. If any part of the selector query changes between requests, the results are undefined.

      • update

        private Boolean update
        Whether to update the index prior to returning the result. Default is true.

      • stable

        private Boolean stable
        Whether or not the view results should be returned from a “stable” set of shards

      • stale

        private MangoQuery.Stale stale
        Combination of update=false and stable=true options. (Default: false)

      • executionStats

        private Boolean executionStats
        Include execution statistics in the query response. (Default: false)
